On 4/20/11 3:22 PM, Muath Alkhalaf wrote:
&gt; OK so let me get this clear.
&gt; First I configure a job through web interface then click on submit job.
&gt; After that I go to the job directory and edit the seeds file.
&gt; Then I go to the console on the web interface and start crawling.

Roughly, yes. You can leave the crawler in the &#39;holding jobs&#39; state 
(don&#39;t hit &#39;start&#39; in the main console window), create your job, edit 
the seeds.txt, and then tell the crawler to start crawling pending jobs.

You can also, on the initial &#39;create new job&#39; screen, hit one of the 
buttons other than &#39;submit job&#39; to view the other configuration pages 
(other than the &#39;settings&#39; fields, which also includes the seeds.txt 
textarea at the bottom). Manually edit the seeds.txt, and only then 
&#39;submit job&#39;.

&gt; One more question, if I initiated a new job based on an old one that has
&gt; a seeds.txt file, is the file going to be copied?

Yes.

&gt; By the way, why there is not anything about this (using seeds.txt) in
&gt; the manual. I think this is very important.

It should be, but the H1 User Manual has always been more of a guide to 
getting started than a complete reference. Also, it hasn&#39;t received 
major updates in a long time – I think its info was most current around 
the 1.8-1.10 timeframe, and I suspect editing large seed lists outside 
the UI was considered a clunky expert trick at the time of its initial 
writing.

More attention is now paid to the H3 User Manual. That lives on the 
project wiki, in the hope that any user who notices an error or omission 
can help fix them directly.

- Gordon @ IA

